                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 18: The government has decided to reduce duty drawbacks  tax refund  by up to 30 per cent. The move will affect exporters in sectors such as leather, textiles and sports goods. The new rates will come into effect from September 20, the Central Board of Excise and Customs said. Duty drawback  refund of import duties on raw materials used in exports  for cotton garments has been reduced to 7.5 per cent against the present rate of 8.8 per cent.                            
	 Calcutta, Sept. 18: The tea industry will start the e-auction of orthodox and Darjeeling tea by the end of this year, Gopal Poddar, chairman of the Calcutta Tea Traders Association, said.                             
	 Calcutta, Sept. 18: Luxury menswear maker Ermenegildo Zegna Group and Reliance Brands Ltd has set up a joint venture to develop the Zegna brand in India.                                                                                                                          
